Nikole Vannest

            Nikole Vannest
          
          
            
              I am a master’s candidate at the University of
              California - Santa Barbara’s Bren School for Environmental
              Science and Management, currently residing in Santa
              Barbara, CA.
              I am currently working on my thesis project - Exploring
              Mountain Lion Connectivity in Central and Southern
              California, in collaboration with The Nature Conservancy
              at the Jack and Laura Dangermond Preserve.
              I love talking about gardening, travel and plant
              ID.
